Project Context
This is a premium single-page website for Dycon (dycon.ie), an Irish building materials company. Built with Vite + React + Tailwind CSS + Three.js (@react-three/fiber, @react-three/drei) + GSAP ScrollTrigger.
Tech Stack — Do Not Suggest Alternatives

React 18 with functional components and hooks
Vite for bundling (not Next.js, not CRA)
Tailwind CSS for styling (not CSS modules, not styled-components)
Three.js via @react-three/fiber and @react-three/drei for 3D
GSAP + ScrollTrigger for scroll animations
Google Fonts: Oswald (headings) + DM Sans (body)

Code Style

Use functional components with hooks
Use const arrow functions for components
Prefer named exports
Use Tailwind utility classes, not custom CSS (except for animations and Three.js)
Keep components in single files (no separate CSS files)
Use refs (useRef) for DOM elements that GSAP targets
Use useEffect with cleanup for all GSAP ScrollTrigger instances
Always use gsap.context() for React cleanup

Three.js Rules

All 3D geometry must use EXACT numeric values, not vague descriptions
When creating curved geometry (TubeGeometry), provide literal Vector3 coordinate arrays
Always include <Environment preset="studio" /> for metallic materials
Use MeshPhysicalMaterial for realistic surfaces (never MeshBasicMaterial)
The PaintCan component uses useFrame for continuous animation — never stop it
Canvas must have gl={{ alpha: true, antialias: true }} for transparent bg
Never add shadows unless explicitly requested

GSAP ScrollTrigger Rules

Always register: gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger)
Always clean up: use gsap.context() in useEffect, return ctx.revert()
Call ScrollTrigger.refresh() after component mount
For animations that should STOP at a position: use onEnter/onLeave callbacks with gsap.killTweensOf(), not continuous scrub
Prefer toggleActions over scrub for discrete state changes (show/hide)
Never create overlapping ScrollTriggers on the same element

Critical Behavioral Rules

Do NOT use browser tools, screenshot tools, or wait commands after changes
Do NOT modify files not mentioned in the prompt
Do NOT add console.log statements unless debugging is requested
Do NOT refactor or rename existing working code unless asked
Do NOT change the colour palette, fonts, or layout unless specifically requested
When fixing a bug, explain what was wrong in a code comment
One task per prompt. Do not scope-creep.

Colour Palette (CSS variables in :root)

--bg-cream: #F5F0EB
--text-primary: #1A1A1A
--text-secondary: #8A8A8A
--green-brand: #2D5A27
--green-accent: #4CAF50
--dark: #1A1A1A
--white: #FFFFFF